f=Brand Studio/nate/marketplace/funnel-analysis/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "funnel-analysis" (Product Faculty PM-Copilot, v2.0.0), fulfilling catalog's funnel-analysis slot ("instrument stages; find largest drop; hypothesize test"). Chosen leaky-bucket prioritization (absolute drop recovery value actionability), per-drop diagnosis table, Step output ending RECOMMENDED EXPERIMENTS which feed directly experiment-backlog's intake, making two skills one loop. NOTES SYSTEM: Step 1's "memory/user-profile.md" "context/company/analytics-baseline.md" source repo's second-brain layout system they resolve kai's brand-context baselines configured metrics sources. Funnel data comes kai (instrumented) operator exports; unmeasurable stages instrumentation finding kai, guess. --> · h1:Funnel Analysis=You analyzing conversion funnel identify users drop off, they drop off, what actions improve overall conversion. Framework: AARRR (Pirate Metrics Acquisition, Activation, Retention, Revenue, Referral), Dave McClure's funnel stages. · h2:Step Load Context=Read `memory/user-profile.md` product stage business model. Read `context/company/analytics-baseline.md` existing conversion benchmarks. · h2:Step Funnel Data Input=Ask user provide funnel data. Accept any format: · h2:Step Funnel Data Input=Step names conversion rates step, Raw numbers (absolute users step), description funnel steps approximate drop-off · h2:Step Funnel Data Input=user describes funnel without numbers, help them estimate identify find data. · h2:Step Calculate Key Metrics=funnel data, calculate: · h2:Step Calculate Key Metrics=**Step-by-step conversion rate:** Users step users step N-1, **Overall funnel conversion:** Users final step users first step, **Absolute drop-off:** Users lost step (in absolute numbers,, **Revenue impact step:** Absolute drop-off revenue converted user value fixing step · h2:Step Identify Biggest Opportunity=Find step highest combination of: Large absolute drop-off (many users lost here) High recovery value (if conversion improved 10%, much total revenue engagement add?) Actionability (is known reason drop? plausible fix?) "leaky bucket" one step that, fixed, improve entire funnel. · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=step 20% drop-off: **What happens step?** (What user do?) **Why users drop here?** (Likely causes look patterns in: friction, value perception, trust signals, cognitive load, technical issues) **What you need know fix it?** (Qualitative insight interviews? Quantitative data heatmaps session recordings? A/B test?) **Common funnel drop diagnoses:** · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| Drop Location \| Likely Cause \| Diagnostic \| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| Landing page → signup \| Value prop unclear; sign-up friction \| Session recording; copy test \| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| Signup → first action \| Onboarding too long; time to value too slow \| Time to first action analysis; session replay \| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| First action → second action \| Not seeing value from first action \| Interview: "what did you expect to happen?" \| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| Free → paid \| Paywall too early; wrong trigger; poor value communication \| Behavioral analysis before upgrade prompt \| · h2:Step Diagnose Major Drop=\| Paid → renewal \| Product not becoming habit; poor ongoing value \| Cohort analysis; engagement depth \| · h2:Step Prioritization Matrix=For each major drop: · h2:Step Prioritization Matrix=Volume impact (absolute users value conversion), Effort fix (quick fix vs. major engineering), Confidence fix work (high evidence vs. hypothesis) · h2:Step Prioritization Matrix=Recommend top 1–2 improvements try next sprint. · h2:Step 7 — Output=Produce: · h2:Step 7 — Output=Funnel visualization (text table step names, conversion rates, absolute drop-off), Revenue/engagement impact step (if baseline data available), Diagnosis major drop likely cause, Prioritized fix recommendations, Recommended experiments (one top-priority step)